                  </persName>
            , desiring two pieces of moreen; I sent them with a bill of parcels; it was brought to me the 11th of July, 1772. (The letter is read.) Some time after 
               <persName id="t17730217-71-person639">
                  Charles
                   Hanforth
               <interp inst="t17730217-71-person639" type="surname" value="Hanforth"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17730217-71-person639" type="given" value="Charles"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17730217-71-person639" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             came to me, and said, sir, I obtained goods in the name of Grantham for a person, it is all a fraud, and the person is now taken up for a like offence, for which he was tried on Saturday at Hick's Hall.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17730217-71-person640">
                  Thomas
                   Grantham
               <interp inst="t17730217-71-person640" type="surname" value="Grantham"></interp>
